<span id="freeTextContainer12923731635718935200">4.5 stars<br/><br/>Both of these essays are brilliant. I do wish that they could have been longer to demonstrate more of her ideas with more text and data. But regardless, this is a great text for anyone interested in discourse or disability studies. There is a lot to think about in our current context as well. <br/><br/>I do think that there were a few points that should have been expanded on a bit more, particularly in AIDS and its Metaphors. But over all, it was still a great read.</span>

