<span id="freeTextContainer6721623629925969533">If you&apos;re at all interested in diseases or the power of language and metaphor, this is a fascinating read. <br/><br/>It&apos;s just a shame that <i>AIDS and Its Metaphors</i> is largely... Not about AIDS, but about influenza, polio, cholera, and other diseases. Then again, Sontag wrote this piece when the US epidemic was still at its peak, so she didn&apos;t have the benefit of hindsight on this one.</span>
  <span id="freeText6721623629925969533" style="display:none">If you're at all interested in diseases or the power of language and metaphor, this is a fascinating read. <br /><br />It's just a shame that <i>AIDS and Its Metaphors</i> is largely... Not about AIDS, but about influenza, polio, cholera, and other diseases. Then again, Sontag wrote this piece when the US epidemic was still at its peak, so she didn't have the benefit of hindsight on this one.</span>
